## Anti-example (❌ do NOT capture this kind of entry here)

```
### BR-XXX — We use JWT for auth
- Rule: All API requests carry a JWT.
```

**Why this is wrong:** "JWT" is a technology choice, not a business invariant.
The actual business invariant is something like "all API requests must be
authenticated to an identifiable user account before any read or write of
PII" — which IS a business rule (LGPD-derived). The mechanism (JWT vs
session vs OAuth) is `architecture.md`.

Rule of thumb: if you can swap the technology and the rule still holds,
the rule is in the right shape. If the rule names a specific library/protocol,
it's misplaced.

